Great upload. Thanks, BhangWalla. It's only a shame that the guidebook is missing though.

very good series.  The prof doesn't just recount history but also the ideas from russian poets, authors and even the common epople that made Russia what it is.  One thing I appreciate about lectures from TTC is that the professors generally put the history in its original narrative context and not just recounting history through a Western views.  ive listened to this TTC lecture series twice.  higly recommended

I strongly recommend people not share this. I got a DMCA letter from them. They will enforce protection of their copyrights. Their stuff is high quality but I chose to delete it all after I got the letter.
